# Flappy Bird Java – System Diagrams

## 1. Game Flow Diagram

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Start Game] --> B[Initialize Game Objects]
    B --> C[Display Start Screen]
    C --> D[Player Presses SPACE]
    D --> E[Game Loop Starts]
    E --> F[Apply Gravity]
    F --> G[Move Bird]
    G --> H[Move Pipes]
    H --> I[Check Collision]
    I -->|Collision| J[Game Over Screen]
    I -->|No Collision| K[Update Score]
    K --> E
    J --> L[Player Chooses Restart]
    L --> B
```

---

## 2. Class Diagram

```mermaid
classDiagram
    class Game
    class Bird
    class Pipe
    class PipeManager
    class Score
    class GamePanel

    Game --> GamePanel
    GamePanel --> Bird
    GamePanel --> PipeManager
    PipeManager --> Pipe
    GamePanel --> Score

    class Bird {
        int x, y
        int velocity
        fly()
        update()
        draw()
    }

    class Pipe {
        int x, gapY
        move()
        draw()
        isPassed()
    }

    class PipeManager {
        List<Pipe> pipes
        spawnPipe()
        update()
        draw()
    }

    class Score {
        int value
        increase()
        reset()
        draw()
    }

    class GamePanel {
        startGame()
        update()
        render()
        checkCollision()
    }
```

---

## 3. Activity Diagram (Gameplay)

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A[Start] --> B[Show Menu]
    B --> C[Press SPACE]
    C --> D[Bird Flies]
    D --> E[Gravity Pulls Down]
    E --> F[Move Pipes]
    F --> G{Collision?}
    G -->|Yes| H[Game Over]
    G -->|No| I[Increase Score]
    I --> D
```

